GUYANA 🇬🇾 Eat the World NYC review: Island Express is the latest outpost in the empire of Sybil Bernard, beloved Guyanese baker and chef who every Caribbean person in South Queens and Brooklyn knows well. From the outside, it somewhat resembles a fast food burger spot, but thankfully the foods are just as good and homemade as her other locations. Start with the delicious rotis and curry, or go straight for the off menu pepper pot, sometimes available even when no special occasion calls for it.
Their bake is to die for!! They also sell great fudge, Guyanese beef patties, and other pastries. Lots of things on the menu are delicious, so I'd highly recommend.

It is straight up DANGEROUS how close this place is to my apartment. Now that I've had a taste of Island Express, I'm not sure if I can eat anything else. I first noticed the spot on an afternoon stroll and was immediately drawn in by the reasonable prices, as well as the promise of delicious baked goods. I got the Pouri wrap with Vegan Curry (only $6.95) and the portion was so big and satiating that I actually had leftovers for the next day. This is coming from a human being who is notoriously insatiable. The side of okra was probably the most delicious I've ever had, and the plantains were killer too. The cherry on top was the pone--a sweet pudding with yucca and coconut--which took this sweet-tooth maniac out of this world, and was unlike anything I've ever had before. Don't pass this place up!
